All A2A protocol requests and responses MUST include the `jsonrpc: "2.0"` field
per the [JSON-RPC 2.0 specification](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification).

**Minimum Valid Request**:
\`\`\`json
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "req-1",
  "method": "message/send",
  "params": {...}
}
\`\`\`

**Minimum Valid Response**:
\`\`\`json
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "req-1",
  "result": {...}
}
\`\`\`
```

## Additional Context

This issue was discovered while implementing strict JSON-RPC validation in an A2A client. The TypeScript interfaces suggested `jsonrpc` was optional, but runtime validation failed when connecting to strict servers.

### Common Mistakes to Avoid

