  "supportsExtendedAgentCard": true,
  "securitySchemes": {
    "google": {
      "openIdConnectSecurityScheme": {
        "openIdConnectUrl": "https://accounts.google.com/.well-known/openid-configuration"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The 2nd example looks correct to me and it's the first one that should be updated to:

```
  "securitySchemes": {
    "google": {
      "openIdConnectSecurityScheme": {
        "openIdConnectUrl": "https://accounts.google.com/.well-known/openid-configuration"
      }
    }
  }
```

However the lack of the `type` fields seems to contradict 

https://github.com/a2aproject/A2A/blob/e8c0f0fd610351987dee368aded7195154699e2b/specification/grpc/a2a.proto#L559-L563

The aforementioned link (https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.2.0.html#security-scheme-object) specifies that `type` is a field that applies to any security schemes.

